# ==============================================================================
# Momentum Note Crafter - Environment Variables Template
# ==============================================================================
#
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values.
# DO NOT commit .env.local to version control (it's in .gitignore).
#
# Usage:
#   cp .env.example .env.local
#   # Edit .env.local with your values
#   npm run dev
#
# ==============================================================================

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API Configuration - Interact.interpublic.com
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These credentials are required for the AI-powered meeting notes generation.
# Contact your IT/DevOps team to obtain these values.

# Client ID for API authentication
# Example: "MeetingNotes"
CLIENT_ID="YourClientID"

# Client Secret for API authentication (keep this secure!)
# Example: "eOk9dez@#En@nWw2w%0N"
CLIENT_SECRET="YourClientSecret"

# Dual Agent Architecture (JSON-only with semantic emphasis)
# Meeting Notes Agent: Generates structured meeting notes with semantic emphasis
# Example: "b8460071-daee-4820-8198-5224fdc99e45"
DEFAULT_NOTES_AGENT_ID="YourMeetingNotesAgentID"

# Interrogation Agent: Answers questions about meeting transcripts
# Example: "f8bf98dc-997c-4993-bbd6-02245b8b0044"
DEFAULT_INTERROGATION_AGENT_ID="YourInterrogationAgentID"

# Legacy Default Bot ID (deprecated - will be removed in future version)
# Example: "64650431-dad7-4b47-8bb1-4a81800f9f5f"
# You can also change agent IDs at runtime via the Settings panel in the app.
DEFAULT_BOT_ID="YourBotID"

# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: Google Gemini API (Not Currently Used)
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This was part of an earlier integration but is not actively used in the
# current version. You can safely leave this as a placeholder.

GEMINI_API_KEY="PLACEHOLDER_API_KEY"

# ==============================================================================
# Notes:
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Environment variables are exposed to the application during build time.
#    For production deployments, these should be configured in your hosting platform.
#
# 2. For production deployments, set these variables in your hosting platform:
#    - Google Cloud Run: Set as environment variables or build-time ENV in Dockerfile
#    - Vercel: Project Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Azure Static Web Apps: Configuration → Application Settings
#    - Netlify: Site Settings → Environment Variables
#
# 3. MSAL Authentication configuration (Azure AD) is in auth/authConfig.ts.
#    You'll need to update the client ID and tenant ID there as well.
#
# 4. For local development:
#    - The Vite dev server runs on http://localhost:5173
#    - API proxy is configured in vite.config.ts
#    - CORS issues are bypassed via the proxy
#
# 5. Security Best Practices:
#    - Never commit .env.local to git
#    - Rotate secrets regularly
#    - Use different credentials for dev/staging/production
#    - Consider using environment-specific .env files:
#      .env.development, .env.production, .env.staging
#
# ==============================================================================
